resource.source:
<objectXMLWrap>
               <did xmlns="urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9">
                  <repository>
                     <corpname>Ursuline College Archives</corpname>
                  </repository>
                  <origination>
                     <persname>Mary Gonzaga Haessly</persname>
                  </origination>
                  <unittitle>Mary Gonzaga Haessly Papers</unittitle>
                  <physdesc>3.5 linear feet</physdesc>
                  <abstract>The Sister Mary Gonzaga Haessly papers consist of two series: Historical Materials and Printed Matter.  The Historical Materials series (1 linear foot) includes Sister Gonzaga's collected papers while serving as faculty and dean at Ursuline College. Materials include correspondence and reports. Of particular note are Sister Gonzaga's handwritten journals and typewritten "Annals of Ursuline College," which detail events and important dates at Ursuline College from 1922-1966.  The Printed Matter (2.5 linear feet) contains various announcements, programs, brochures, publications, and clippings that Sister Gonzaga collected and organized while at Ursuline College.</abstract>
                  <unitid>PP.007</unitid>
                  <langmaterial>The records are in <language>English</language>
                  </langmaterial>
                  <unitdate>1922-1968</unitdate>
               </did>
            </objectXMLWrap>
resource.title: Mary Gonzaga Haessly Papers 1922-1968
resource.abstract: The Sister Mary Gonzaga Haessly papers consist of two series: Historical Materials and Printed Matter.  The Historical Materials series (1 linear foot) includes Sister Gonzaga's collected papers while serving as faculty and dean at Ursuline College. Materials include correspondence and reports. Of particular note are Sister Gonzaga's handwritten journals and typewritten "Annals of Ursuline College," which detail events and important dates at Ursuline College from 1922-1966.  The Printed Matter (2.5 linear feet) contains various announcements, programs, brochures, publications, and clippings that Sister Gonzaga collected and organized while at Ursuline College.
